CAT(1)

NAME
    cat - print a file

SYNOPSIS
    cat [path]

DESCRIPTION
    cat writes the contents of path to standard output. With no path, it reads
    from standard input.

    cat performs no formatting; bytes are copied as-is.

EXAMPLES
    cat /var/log/boot.txt
    cat /usr/share/man/man1/cat.1

SEE ALSO
    more(1), fsread(1)
